The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 London, Aug.4: HSBC has reported a 28 per cent fall in its first-half profit, as a $14-billion hit on bad debts on US home loans and asset writedowns offset strong Asian growth. HSBC said pre-tax profit for the six months ended June 30 was $10.2 billion, down from $14.2 billion a year before. The average forecast was $10.1 billion. By 1100 GMT, HSBCs London-listed shares were down 2.4 per cent at 817 pence, paring earlier gains and underperforming a flat broad British share index.                            
	 London, Aug. 4: Oil fell below $120 a barrel today, pressured by evidence of rising Opec output in the midst of declining demand in the US and Europe. US light crude fell $4.10 to $121 a barrel by 1640 GMT after slipping as low as $119.50.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 4: The government has decided to withdraw the benefit under which exporters earned interest on exchange earners foreign currency accounts from November 1.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 4: State-run NHPC has convened a board meeting tomorrow to approve its initial public offering along with a 5 per cent disinvestment of government stake.                             
	 Calcutta, Aug. 4: Indian Overseas Bank will open a branch in Patuli tomorrow. Y.L. Madan, executive director of the bank, will be present at the inauguration.                                                                                                                         
